modules.description: Provides functions to parse and enforce resource limits from system-specific data structures, including CPU time, memory, and file descriptors. Operates on opaque limit representations and raw integer values to apply constraints during process execution. Used to restrict process behavior in sandboxed environments or resource-constrained deployments.

Provides functions to execute code with enforced memory constraints, including a main execution function that takes a callback and enforces limits on heap and stack usage. Operates with integers representing memory sizes in kilobytes and megabytes, and string-based context retrieval. Used to safely run potentially memory-intensive operations in environments with strict resource controls.

Provides functions to manage and enforce memory limits during test execution, working with test configurations and execution contexts. It includes a list of tests that are annotated with memory constraints. Used to ensure that specific tests do not exceed predefined memory thresholds during runtime.

Provides functions to execute a computation with a time limit, returning `None` if the deadline is exceeded. Works with `timeout_info` to track timing details and `float` or `float option` to specify durations. Used to safely wrap long-running operations in network requests or file processing.
